    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-07-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Record of the proceedings of the tribunal of arbitration at
                        the eleventh conference, held at Geneva, in Switzerland, on the</hi> 11<hi
                        rend="italic">th of July</hi>, 1872.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>Geneva, Switzerland</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1872-07-11">July 11, 1872</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The conference was held pursuant to adjournment. All the arbitrators and the
                    agents of the two governments were present.</p>
                <p>The protocol of the last conference was read and approved, and was signed by the
                    president and secretary of the tribunal, and the agents of the two
                    governments.</p>
                <p>On the proposal of Sir Alexander Cockburn it was decided that the written
                    opinions or statements read by the arbitrators to the tribunal should be
                    printed, and distributed to the arbitrators and to the agents and counsel of the
                    two governments.</p>
                <pb facs="0041" n="29" xml:id="pg_29"/>
                <p>The tribunal then proceeded with the consideration of the case of the Florida.
                        <seg type="margin">The Florida.</seg>
                </p>
                <p>The conference was adjourned until Friday, the 19th instant, at 1 o’clock in the
                    afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>FREDERICK SOLOPIS.</item>
                            <item>J. C. BANCROFT DAVIS.</item>
                            <item>TENTERDEN.</item>
                            <item>ALEX. FAVROT, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
